<paragraph blockId="3.[151,1436,1926,2024]" lastBlockId="4.[151,1437,151,792]" lastPageId="4" lastPageNumber="39" pageId="3" pageNumber="38">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,473,1926,1951]" pageId="3" pageNumber="38">Brachypterous female.</emphasis>
Size (n= 
<number box="[589,600,1927,1951]" pageId="3" pageNumber="38" value="1.0">1</number>
): Length, 
<quantity box="[722,828,1927,1951]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="8.16" pageId="3" pageNumber="38" unit="mm" value="8.16">8.16 mm</quantity>
. Width, 
<quantity box="[930,1037,1927,1951]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="5.44" pageId="3" pageNumber="38" unit="mm" value="5.44">5.44 mm</quantity>
. Coloration and setation generally same as for male, except abdominal paired yellowish areas on either side of the midline on terga IV–VI (
<figureCitation box="[1352,1423,1963,1987]" captionStart="FIGURES 1 – 2" captionStartId="2.[151,264,1120,1143]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,193,1097]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[151,1436,193,1099]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURES 1 – 2. Habitus of Aphelocheirus kaygieyess n. sp. (1) male, (2) female." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/202274/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="38">
Fig. 
<number box="[1406,1423,1963,1987]" pageId="3" pageNumber="38" value="2.0">2</number>
</figureCitation>
). Yellow lateral and posterolateral areas of abdominal segments more pronounced. Subgenital plate yellow basally, brown distally; broadly triangular; sides shallowly concave, gradually converging to broadly-rounded point (
<figureCitation captionStart="FIGURES 3 – 4" captionStartId="2.[151,264,1887,1910]" captionTargetBox="[151,1409,1192,1866]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[151,1436,1192,1867]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURES 3 – 4. Aphelocheirus kaygieyess n. sp. (3) male genital capsule with aedeagus and parameres, (4) ventral aspect of posterior abdominal segments of female." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/202275/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="39">
Fig. 
<number box="[151,168,188,212]" pageId="4" pageNumber="39" value="4.0">4</number>
</figureCitation>
); width 
<quantity box="[264,368,188,212]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.38" pageId="4" pageNumber="39" unit="mm" value="1.38">1.38 mm</quantity>
, length 
<quantity box="[461,566,188,212]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.1" pageId="4" pageNumber="39" unit="mm" value="1.1">1.10 mm</quantity>
; with lateral trichobothria 
<number box="[871,881,188,212]" pageId="4" pageNumber="39" value="1.0">1</number>
/ 
<number box="[891,907,188,212]" pageId="4" pageNumber="39" value="4.0">4</number>
distance from externally visible base to apex; recumbent setae throughout; group of long, stout setae just basad of apex on either side of midline. Sternum III without posteromedial protuberance. Posterior margins of sterna IV–V deeply concave and VI straight to slightly concave in middle third (
<figureCitation box="[431,500,295,319]" captionStart="FIGURES 3 – 4" captionStartId="2.[151,264,1887,1910]" captionTargetBox="[151,1409,1192,1866]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[151,1436,1192,1867]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURES 3 – 4. Aphelocheirus kaygieyess n. sp. (3) male genital capsule with aedeagus and parameres, (4) ventral aspect of posterior abdominal segments of female." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/202275/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="39">
Fig. 
<number box="[483,500,295,319]" pageId="4" pageNumber="39" value="4.0">4</number>
</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="4.[151,1437,151,792]" box="[199,566,331,356]" pageId="4" pageNumber="39">
